stimulus_1.text:
A rectangle measures 10 cm by 8 cm.

Squares of side 1 cm are cut from each corner of the rectangle.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

The volume of a rectangular prism is found by multiplying the length by breadth by height.

success.question_text: What happens to the area and perimeter of the new rectangle compared to the old rectangle?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Problem Solving

stimulus_2.text: A new rectangle is formed by halving the length and doubling the breadth.

choice_1.label: The area is the same and the perimeter decreases.

choice_2.label: The area is the same and the perimeter increases.

choice_3.label: The area and perimeter are the same.

choice_4.label: The area decreases and the perimeter is the same.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

A set of scales is used to compare the mass of two objects. When one side of the scales is lower, the object on that side is heavier than the object on the other side.

success.question_text: Using your own weight as a guide, the total weight of all 80 students could be about
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Mass

stimulus_2.text: Eighty Year 6 students are assembled at school.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

The weight of students in Year 6 will vary. It doesn’t matter what you weigh, 80 students of the same weight will be around 3.5 tonnes in total.

success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Time

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

When subtracting time, it is easiest to subtract the hours and minutes separately.

e.g. Subtract 2 h and 45 min from 9:30. Now 9:30 minus 2 h is 7:30. Now subtract 30 min to make 7:00 and then another 15 min. This means the answer is 6:45.

success.question_text: What is the slowest speed that Austin can travel to arrive on time for his appointment if Sunshine Bay is 50 kilometres away?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Speed

stimulus_2.text: Austin has an appointment in Sunshine Bay in 40 minutes.

review_3.column_1_text:
Austin needs to travel 50 kilometres in 40 minutes.

This means he needs to travel 25 kilometres in 20 minutes.

So he needs to travel 75 kilometres in 60 minutes.

Austin needs to travel at 75 km/h.

Tip

Often it is easier to think logically about speed rather than just remember formulas.

success.question_text: If he can ride six times as fast as he can walk, how long will it take Layoun to ride from his home to his grandparents’ home?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Speed

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Don’t be tricked by extra information. For example, in this question it didn’t matter what the distance was.

stimulus_1.text: A butcher shop, a newsagency and a bank are all on the same side of a street. The butcher shop is 150 metres from the newsagency and the bank is 260 metres from the butcher shop.

success.question_text: If Guy runs at 12 km/h, how long will it take him to run five laps of the sports field?

stimulus_2.text:

He trains by running around the outside of a sports field that is in the shape of a rectangle.

The rectangular field is 200 metres long and 100 metres wide.

success.question_text: About how far from Kilkivan are both the car and truck when they pass?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Graphs

stimulus_1.text: Kilkivan is 240 kilometres from Brisbane. A car leaves Brisbane to travel to Kilkivan. At the same time, a truck leaves Kilkivan to travel to Brisbane. The distance that both the car and truck are from Brisbane at different times is shown on the graph.

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

The point where the car and truck will pass is when they are both the same distance from Brisbane.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Carefully read the titles and scales on the axes of a graph.

success.question_text: How far is the truck from Brisbane when the car reaches Kilkivan?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Graphs

stimulus_1.text: Kilkivan is 240 kilometres from Brisbane. A car leaves Brisbane to travel to Kilkivan. At the same time, a truck leaves Kilkivan to travel to Brisbane. The distance that both the car and truck are from Brisbane at different times is shown on the graph.

review_3.column_1_text:
From the graph, this is when the truck is 60 kilometres from Brisbane.

Tip

Carefully read the titles and scales on the axes of a graph.

success.question_text: What is the smallest length of material Natalie will need to make the border?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Perimeter

stimulus_2.text:
Natalie has a table that is 2.5 metres long and 1.5 metres wide. A tablecloth sits on the table with 15 centimetres hanging down over each of its edges.

Natalie has another table that is slightly larger and for which this tablecloth is too small. She intends to sew a border on the cloth so that it will exactly fit the top of the larger table.

Natalie needs to obtain some material for the border.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Read the question carefully, again and again if necessary.

success.question_text: What is the thickness of 500 sheets of paper?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Problem Solving

stimulus_2.text: A sheet of paper is 0.07 millimetres thick.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Use the conversion 10 millimetres (mm) = 1 centimetre (cm).

To change millimetres to centimetres, divide by 10.

To change centimetres to millimetres, multiply by 10.
